rComments: Math 104 with dr. Walls was amazing. I truly enjoyed the course!
Best prof ever. His notes are extremely helpful and Must go to his reveiw session.
Definitely one of the Best math profs ever.
Patrick is really helpful and is always willing to take up questions and provide additional math resources. Picky about lecture halls though :)
Patrick is very nice, willing to answer questions, and helpful in lecture. His notes are very well organized and he has a wealth of knowledge. Definitely one of he best Math profs!

An extremely nice and helpful professor, goes beyond what any teacher at the undergraduate level is required to do. The last lesson prior to the first test, he devoted a portion of his time outside the classroom to help kids that needed clarification or additional help on confused concepts. He is helpful and altruistic, so make the best use of him.

A superb instructor. His lectures are usually paced just right. He takes time to explain/clarify things. He is very helpful during office hours and has no problem going overtime. Midterm and Final are quite consistent with questions from assignments.

Amazing instructor. His lectures are clear and notes are well organized. Very approachable after lectures and during office hours. He also cares for his students a lot; when I missed part of his lectures due to schedule conflict (midterms for another course), he photocopied the notes for me!
